Subject: Remove local=1 from inspector genrule for RBE compatibility

The generated_inspector_files genrule has local=1 which forces local
execution. In cross-platform RBE (macOS host -> Linux target), all tool
binaries and Python interpreters are for Linux, so local execution fails
with "Exec format error". Removing local=1 allows the genrule to run
remotely on Linux containers where the tools can actually execute.

diff --git a/BUILD.bazel b/BUILD.bazel
--- a/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/BUILD.bazel
@@ -4411,7 +4411,6 @@ genrule(
            --config $(location :src/inspector/inspector_protocol_config.json) \
            --config_value protocol.path=$(location :include/js_protocol.pdl) \
            --output_base $(@D)/src/inspector",
-    local = 1,
     message = "Generating inspector files",
     tools = [
         ":code_generator",
